The paper deals with information spreading in networks, which is a topic that falls under distributed computing (cs.DC). The use of algebraic gossip and spanning tree protocols suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of social and information networks (cs.SI), networked systems (cs.NI), systems and control (cs.SY), and information theory (cs.IT).
